    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you, but it feels like you're dismissing a lot of real concerns people have about their jobs and local manufacturing being hollowed out. if a country is intentionally undercutting our prices to destroy our industrial base, isn't it just common sense to use tariffs as a defensive tool? it seems like you're prioritizing abstract economic theories over the actual survival of these industries.",
